  					props="autonumber">5301.603-3</ph> Appointment</title>
			<conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
				<ol class="- topic/ol ">
					<li class="- topic/li ">
						<p class="- topic/p ">(b)  Issuing authorities identified in <xref outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
    								class="- topic/xref "
    								base="DFARS_5301_603_1"
    								href="5301_603-1.dita#AFFARS_5301_603_1">5301.603-1</xref> above may delegate the purchase authority described in FAR <ph outputclass="FAR"
  								class="- topic/ph ">1.603-3</ph>(b) and DFARS <ph outputclass="DFARS"
  								class="- topic/ph ">201.603-3</ph>(b), to non-contracting DoD civilian employees and members of the U.S. Armed Forces, such as transportation personnel, medical supply personnel, librarians, and chiefs of construction management, provided: <ol class="- topic/ol ">
								<li outputclass="List 2"
  									class="- topic/li ">
									<p outputclass="List 2"
 										class="- topic/p ">(1)  The written delegation specifies a dollar limit per transaction (e.g., per order, per call); the method(s) of award; and the supplies, equipment and/or non-personal services, to include construction, related to the individualâ€™s specialty that may be procured.  For example, librarians may buy books, but not construction materials or services; and, </p>
								</li>
								<li outputclass="List 2"
  									class="- topic/li ">
									<p outputclass="List 2"
 										class="- topic/p ">(2)  Personnel have completed contracting training commensurate with the type of instrument(s) authorized to process and level of responsibility delegated.</p>
								</li>
							</ol>
						</p>
					</li>
				</ol>
				<p outputclass="Normal"
 					class="- topic/p ">See <ph outputclass="AFICC PGI"
